        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2020-02-13 10:19:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nI don't see the use of EXT4_DIR_ENTRY_LEN() anywhere in the upstream kernel yet.  That looks like it is from Artems unlanded dirdata patch.  While it would be great to get that patch landed (in the Lustre tree, and also upstream), it seems confusing to tie this to the change described in the commit message, which is a few lines in __ext4_check_dir_entry()?\n\nIf we want to update the Lustre ext4-data-in-dirent.patch to match the changes that Artem made for upstream submission, that should be done as a separate patch that is clearly described as such.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
